<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="796" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d796">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-11-07"><hi rend="italic">November 7,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hunter reports that Mr. Hay’s rights to indemnity, which he demanded
                            in accordance with instruction No. 195 of October 6, are denied by
                            Guatemalan Government, which offers to submit to an arbitral tribunal
                            all disputed points for the determination of the question as to the
                            existence of rights to damages, and if so, the amount of such
                            damages.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>